<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="COL" stage="Rev" version="B">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:54:39Z" when="2009-10-02 03:54:39Z" stage="Draft">initial draft by Pdt. Max Jacob (almarhum); C&amp;B Grimes, team advisors; this book, C. Grimes; Ex. Summ. is point for initial comparison, if there are questions re: exegesis; other resources: GNT; NLT, HCE; Bruce, New International Commentary on NT, Colossians (1988); Wright, Tyndale Commentary on Colossians (1986); exegetical team check in Darwin, Aug 2004 with Mus and June; Read through + revisions with Barbara &amp; team, Aug 04; UNS checked in Kupang by Mus, 31 Aug - 4 Sep (details below); BT by Chuck; consultant checked by Marge Crofts in Kupang, 8 October 2004 (Mus, June, Chuck); file cleaned up &amp; notes added, checked devil, &amp; explication of Christ, Sept 2005 by Chuck; read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:58:58Z" when="2014-02-24 10:58:58Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 8 October 2004 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: Transl Cons ReporKMepis.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-20 02:17:56Z" when="2015-01-20 02:17:56Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina, at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Kolose</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Paulus pung surat<bt>Paulus' letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">kasi orang parcaya di kota<bt>to the believers (believing people) in the city of</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Kolose<bt>Kolose</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus buka dia pung surat<bt>Paulus opens his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Salam dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan Allah sandiri yang pili ame sang beta ko jadi Yesus Kristus pung utusan. Di sini ju ada kotong pung sodara Timotius yang titip salam kasi bosong.<bt>Greetings from me, Paulus. God himself is the one who chose me to become Yesus Kristus' *apostle (=emissary, one sent w/mission, comission). Here there is also our-inc sibling Timotius who sends greetings to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Paul, apostle of Christ Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Paul, apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God and Timothy the brother,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Beta tulis ini surat kasi sang bosong, andia Tuhan Allah pung orang di kota Kolose, yang bekin iko tarús Yesus Kristus pung jalan idop.<bt>I write this letter to you-pl, that is God's people in the city of Kolose, who continue to follow Yesus Kristus' way of life (lifestyle, character, values).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***compare these address tweaks with other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">***compare these address tweaks with other Pauline letters</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Botong minta ko Tuhan Allah, kotong pung Bapa, kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>We-exc ask that God, our-inc Father, show His goodness/grace/kindness to you, so that you can live in safety/security (situational), peace (relational), and calm (inner peace). [EXEG: word study on /eirene/ and formula we use for Paul's greetings.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: to the saints and faithful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: to the saints and faithful brothers in Christ in Colossae, grace to you and peace from God our Father.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus sambayang kasi sang orang parcaya di Kolose<bt>Paulus prays for the believers in Kolose</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Tiap kali botong di sini sambayang kasi sang bosong, botong minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, andia kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung Bapa.<bt>Each time we-exc here pray for you, we give thanks to God, who is Father of our-inc Boss, Yesus Kristus. [EXEG: Gk is ambiguous “we give thanks … always for you praying”. (See Ex. Summ. on varying ideas of what ‘always’ is modifying.) Problem with RL grammar (as in many lgs) is dative-benefactive (to/for) are conflated—but defaults to dative. So “pray for you” vs “pray to you” is the same. “Pray mentioning you” is how we have to distinguish to mean “pray for you”. But this sets up other ocmplications like this one where it comes out “Each time we-exc here pray, we mention you, (and) we give thanks to God…” “Each time” has its own challenges.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We always thank God the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We always thank God the Father and our Lord Jesus Christ when we pray for you,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sang Tuhan Allah, yang jadi Bapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">sang Tuhan Allah, yang jadi Bapa dari kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te botong su dengar banya hal so'al bosong pung parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, deng so'al bosong pung sayang deng hati bae kasi orang parcaya samua.<bt>Cuz we have heard many things about your faith/belief/trust in Yesus Kristus, and about your love/pity and goodness/kindness/generosity toward all believers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because we have heard of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because we have heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and the love which you have for all the saints,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bosong bekin bagitu, tagal bosong tau ada hal-hal bae yang tasimpan kasi bosong di sorga. Ini hal dong, bosong parná dengar dari kata-kata yang batúl, andia Tuhan pung Kabar Bae,<bt>You do that, because you know there are good things, which are stored-away for you in heaven. These things, you have heard from the true words/message/sayings, that is God2's Good News,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elpidos: hope, expectation, something hoped for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">elpidos: hope, expectation, something hoped for apokeimai: be put away, stored up, laid up, reserved<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: because of the hope stored up for you in heaven. Of this you have heard before in the word of truth, the Good News.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />yang orang su pi kasi tau sang bosong dari dolu. Itu Kabar Bae su tasiar pi mana-mana di ini dunya, deng dapa hasil yang bae, tagal dia roba orang pung idop jadi bae. Bosong pung idop ju baroba jadi bae bagitu, mulai dari hari partama bosong dengar itu Kabar Bae, deng mangarti batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung hati bae.<bt>which people have gone to tell/explain to you from long ago. That Good News has already spread everywhere/all over this world, and has gotten good results/produced good fruits, because it changes people's lives to become good. Your lives have also been changed becoming good like that, beginning from the first day you heard that Good News, and truly understood God's goodness/grace/kindness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareimi: be present, come and stay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">pareimi: be present, come and stay karpophorew: bear fruit, change people's conduct and character<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>auksanw: grow, increase, extend its influence epiginwskw: know, understand<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: It has come to you, just as also in the whole world it is producing fruit and growing, so also among you, from the day you heard and understood the grace of God in truth.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Bosong su balajar ini hal dong dari bu Epafras, andia botong pung tamán karjá yang botong sayang. Te dia rajin kasi jalan tarús Kristus pung karjá di bosong pung teng-tenga.<bt>You have learned these things from elder.brother Epafras, that is our fellow worker whom we love. Cuz he is diligent/industrious to keep carrying out Kristus' work among you. [TEXT: Gk “for you” reading is almost certain (also followed by NRSV, NLT, CEV, TB2); “for us” reading is less supported, although followed by NIV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You learned it from Epaphras"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You learned it from Epaphras our dear fellow servant, who is a faithful servant of Christ for you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 4:12, Filemon 23</note><v n="8" />Dia ada carita kasi botong di sini so'al bosong pung sayang, yang Tuhan pung Roh su kasi sang bosong.<bt>He has been telling us here about your love/pity, which God2's Spirit has given you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="delow: reveal, make clear LITERALLY: He"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">delow: reveal, make clear LITERALLY: He revealed to us your love in the spirit.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Tagal itu, mulai dari kali partama botong dengar so'al bosong, botong sambayang tarús-tarús kasi sang bosong. Botong minta sang Tuhan Allah ko bosong bisa kanál batúl-batúl Dia pung mau, deng bosong bisa mangarti banya hal, iko apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ajar sang bosong.<bt>Because of that, beginning from the first time we heard about you-pl, we have continued to pray for you. We ask God that you can truly know His will, and you can understand many things, according to what it is that God2's Spirit teaches you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because of this we also,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because of this we also, from the day we heard, do not stop praying for you and asking that you may be filled with the knowledge of his will in all spiritual wisdom and understanding.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Deng bagitu, bosong bisa idop pantas, deng bawa Tuhan Allah pung nama bae. Deng bosong ju bisa bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati dalam samua hal. Kalo bosong kasi tunju hati bae sang orang, nanti Tuhan kasi bosong hasil yang bae. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa tamba kanál sang Tuhan.<bt>In that way, you can live appropriately, and bring/carry God's good name/reputation. And you can also make God2's liver happy in all matters. If you show your goodness/kindness to people, then God2 will give you good results. In that way, you can increasingly know God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: [We pray that you may]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: [We pray that you may] live worthy of the Lord, pleasing him in everything, bearing fruit in every good work, and increasing in the knowledge of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11-13" />Botong ju sambayang minta Tuhan Allah kasi Dia pung kuasa yang hebat, ko bosong bisa tanggong samua hal deng sabar. Botong minta ko bosong pung hati bisa ponu deng rasa sanáng, ko bosong minta tarima kasi tarús-tarús sang Allah Bapa. Te Dia su buka jalan ko bosong bisa tarima bagian dari pusaka di sorga. Itu pusaka tu, Dia kasi sang samua orang yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Te Dia su kasi lapás sang kotong dari kuasa galáp, ais kasi maso sang kotong jadi Yesus Kristus pung orang, ko tenga dalam taráng. Dia ju angka sang Yesus Kristus, ko jadi kotong pung Raja. Yesus tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana sayang.<bt>We also pray asking God to give His amazing power/authority so you can bear/carry/endure all things with patience. We ask that your livers can be full of happiness, so you will continually give thanks to Father God. Cuz (elaboration) He has opened the way so you can receive (your) portion of inheritance in heaven. That inheritance, He gives to all people who believe in Yesus Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) He has already freed/released us-inc from the powers of darkness [NOTE: yes, they use this phrase all the time; associated with evil spirits], and entered us into becoming Yesus Kristus' people, to live in the light. He has also elevated/appointed Yesus Kristus, to be/become our-inc King. That Yesus, is God's beloved Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Verses coalesced because the &quot;light&quot; metaphor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">Verses coalesced because the "light" metaphor doesn't mean anything. Light and darkness are interpreted here as moral, because we're implied to have been "under the power of darkness," so it's probably not the understanding reading. LITERALLY: [That you may] be strengthened with all power according to his glorious might for all endurance and patience.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: With joy thank the Father, who has made us able to share the inheritance of the saints in light. LITERALLY: He rescued us from the power of darkness and transferred us into the kingdom of his beloved Son.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te Tuhan Allah su sarakan Dia pung Ana tu, ko tabús ame sang kotong, deng hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God has turned-over/surrendered/given up that Child of His, to (fully) *redeem us and wipe away our-inc wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;let us guys go?&quot; 2:13, 3:13"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">"let us guys go?" 2:13, 3:13 NOT HERE. "pay the price" covers that component of forgiveness, so "let go" would be overkill. LITERALLY: In Christ we have redemption, the forgiveness of sins.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 1:7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus tu, paling tinggi dari samua<bt>That Kristus, is highest of all</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Kristus tu, satu model deng Tuhan Allah,<bt>That Kristus, is the same model/type/form as God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang manusia sonde bisa dapa lia.<bt>who humans cannot see.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia su ada lebe dolu dari samua,<bt>He already existed before everything else,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Dia jadi Bos dari samua yang Tuhan Allah su bekin.<bt>and He is Boss of everything that God has created.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He is the image of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of all creation,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Te Tuhan Allah pake sang Dia<bt>Cuz (backgrounded reason) God used Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko bekin ame langit deng bumi pung isi samua.<bt>to create all the contents of heaven and earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia bekin hal-hal yang manusia bisa dapa lia,<bt>He made the things that humans can see,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng yang manusia sonde bisa dapa lia.<bt>and that humans cannot see.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Conto ke, dong yang pegang parenta, dong yang pegang kuasa,<bt>For example, those who hold rule/government, those who hold power/authority,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">raja-raja dong, deng bos-bos dong.<bt>kings, and bosses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang Tuhan Allah mau bekin,<bt>Everything that God wants to do/make,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia bekin kasi sang Yesus Kristus,<bt>He did/made for Yesus Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng Yesus yang karjá itu samua ju.<bt>and Yesus is also the one who did all that work. [EXEG: Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="List of terms matched with Eph"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">List of terms matched with Eph 1:21. LITERALLY: because in him all things in heaven and earth were created, visible and invisible, whether thrones or lords or rulers or powers/authorities; all things were created by him and for him.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Waktu samua yang laen balóm ada,<bt>When everything else did not yet exist,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Dia su ada memang.<bt>nevertheless He already existed beforehand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang ada, ta'ika deng Dia,<bt>Everything that exists, is bound/joined to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Dia yang ator sang dong.<bt>And He is the one who arranges/regulates them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'ika ; pegang ; tenun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">ta'ika ; pegang ; tenun</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He is before all things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He is before all things and all things hold together in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Dia yang jadi Kapala kasi samua orang parcaya,<bt>He is the one who is Head of all believers,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kephale: head = source"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">kephale: head = source</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng orang parcaya dong jadi sama ke Dia pung badan.<bt>And believers are like His body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***3rd line deleted from earlier draft"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">***3rd line deleted from earlier draft "who listen to/obey Him"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Dia yang kasi jalan samua-samua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who carries out/sets in motion everything. [EXEG: Ex. Summ has a series of conflicting options and vague statements about whether the focus is Christ or the church at the beginning of the verse. We take the focus of the passage as Christ, and the overall theme the supremacy of Christ. This focus is reinforced by the grammar repeatedly structured “He is the …” So I take this clause as connected to the church in the previous two lines, but not focused on the church—the higher level focus is still on Christ here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dari samua yang mati ais idop kambali,<bt>From/among everything/everyone that dies and then lives again,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang paling pantíng,<bt>He is the most important,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko biar Dia yang paling tinggi dari samua.<bt>so that He is the highest of/over all.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He is the head of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He is the head of the body, the church. He is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, that he may be first in everything.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 1:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19" />Samua yang ada dalam Tuhan Allah pung diri,<bt>Everything which exists in God's Being/Self,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ada dalam Kristus pung diri ju,<bt>also exists in Kristus' Being/Self.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng itu bekin Tuhan sanáng.<bt>and that makes God happy,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***restructured"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">***restructured</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because in him [God] was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because in him [God] was pleased to have all the fullness dwell.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="20" />Tuhan Allah pake sang Yesus Kristus,<bt>God used Yesus Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko badame deng samua yang Dia su bekin.<bt>to bring relational-peace/reconciliation with everything that He has created.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia kasi Dia pung Ana,<bt>He gave His Child,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko jadi korban yang kasi tumpa Dia pung dara,<bt>to be a sacrifice which spilled His blood,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng mati di kayu palang,<bt>and died on a *cross,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko biar samua yang ada di langit,<bt>so that everything that exists in heaven,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng samua di bumi,<bt>and everything on earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">bisa badame kambali deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>can be reconciled/at peace again with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bae yang ada di bumi, pake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">bae yang ada di bumi, pake Kristus pung dara yang tapo'a di kayu palang.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and through him to reconcile"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and through him to reconcile all things to himself, making peace through the blood of his cross, whether things on earth or things in heaven.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dolu bosong sandiri idop di luar, jao dari Tuhan Allah. Bosong bamusu deng Dia, ais idop tapisa dari Dia, tagal bosong pung hati busuk deng bosong pung bekin jahat ada malawan sang Dia tarús.<bt>Formerly you yourselves lived on the outside, far from God. You were enemies/opposing Him, and so lived separated from Him, because your rotten livers (scheming/plotting/evil intent) and your evil deeds, were opposing/rebelling against Him continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Once you were alienated and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Once you were alienated and enemies in your minds by your evil deeds,</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Biar bagitu, ma sakarang Dia yang su buka jalan ko kotong bisa badame kambali deng Dia. Te Dia yang utus Dia pung Ana ko jadi manusia. Deng Dia yang kasi Dia pung Ana tu, ko jadi korban, deng mati di kayu palang ko kotong bisa badame kambali deng Dia. Yesus Kristus bekin bagitu, ko Dia bisa antar bawa sang kotong pi badiri di Tuhan Allah pung muka, ko jadi orang barisi, deng hati lurus, yang sonde ada pung sala apa-apa lai.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless now He is the one who has opened the way so we-inc can be reconciled/relational peace with Him again. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who sent/commissioned His Child to become a human. And He is the one who allowed that Child of His to become a sacrifice, and die on the cross so we could be reconciled with Him again. Yesus Kristus does that, so He can escort us to go stand before God, to be clean/holy/pure people, with straight/right/honest livers, who have no wrong anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: but now he has reconciled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: but now he has reconciled you by Christ's physical body through death, to present you holy in his sight, blameless and without accusation,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Pokonya, bosong musti batahan tarús deng bosong pung parcaya. Pegang karás ko jang tagoyang! Jang ondor dari itu Kabar Bae, yang bosong tarima waktu bosong dengar partama kali tu. Te bosong bisa basandar di itu Kabar Bae. Orang su pi kasi tau itu Kabar Bae di mana-mana di ini dunya. Deng Tuhan ada utus sang beta, Paulus, ko beta ju pi kasi tau itu Kabar Bae.<bt>The important thing is, you-pl must keep enduring/persevering in your faith/belief/trust. Hold firm so you don't be shaken/moved/waver! Do not retreat/shy away from that Good News, which you received the first time you heard it. Cuz (elaboration) you can depend/lean/hope on that News. People have gone to tell that Good News all over the world. And God2 has commissioned me, Paulus, so I also go tell that Good News. [NOTE to daughter translations (ALT): Jang ondor dari itu Kabar Bae, yang jadi bosong pung tampa basandar, yang bosong tarima waktu bosong dengar partama kali tu.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** hope of the gospel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">*** hope of the gospel</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: provided you continuue in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: provided you continuue in the faith, stable and steadfast, not shifting from the hope of the Good News which you heard, which has been preached to every creature under heaven, of which I, Paul, became aa minister/servant.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus karjá ko layani Tuhan pung orang dong<bt>Paulus works to serve God2's people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu Kristus idop di ini dunya, Dia dapa banya sangsara. Deng sakarang beta ju ada pikol sangsara macam-macam. Biar bagitu ju, ma beta pung hati sanáng tarús. Kalo ada orang yang musti dapa sangsara, na, biar beta yang iko pikol itu sangsara kasi sang dong, sama ke Kristus pikol sangsara kasi Dia pung orang dong. Te Dia pung orang dong jadi sama ke Dia pung badan.<bt>[NOTE: Structure follows HCE] When Kristus lived on this earth, He got/experienced much suffering/difficulty. And now I am also bearing various sorts of difficulty. Even that being the case, nevertheless my liver continues to be happy. If there is someone who must experience suffering, na, just let me be the one to bear that suffering for them, just like Kristus bore suffering for His people. Cuz His people are like His body. [EXEG: See discussion in Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now I rejoice in sufferings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now I rejoice in sufferings for you, and I complete that which is lacking in my flesh/body of the afflictions of Christ, for his body's sake, which is the church.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Tuhan Allah su kasi beta tugas ko layani Dia pung orang dong. Andia ko beta ajar Dia pung Kata-kata kasi bosong sampe alus-alus.<bt>God has given me work-responsibility to serve His people. That is why I teach His Words/Sayings to you in fine detail.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have become its servant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have become its servant by the assignment God gave me to fully present to you the word of God,</Message></Annotation><v n="26-27" />Dari mula-mula, orang dengar Tuhan pung Kata-kata dong. Ma dong balóm mangarti itu Kata-kata pung maksud deng taráng-taráng, te itu maksud masi tasambunyi. Ma sakarang, Tuhan su putus ko buka itu maksud kasi sang Dia pung orang dong. Deng Dia pung maksud tu, kabar yang talalu hebat kasi sang samua suku-bangsa di ini dunya. Itu kabar yang hebat tu, andia:<bt>From the beginning, people heard God2's Words/Sayings/Message. But they did not yet understand the purpose/intention of that Words/Sayings/Message clearly, cuz that purpose was still hidden. But now, God2 has decided to open/reveal that purpose to His people. [EXEG: Gk /mysterion/ "mystery which has been revealed" resonates nicely with KM /maksud/ "purpose/intention" in the sense that it is clear to the Actor, but can be hidden, unclear, and revealed, or made clear to others.] And that purpose of His, is news which is absolutely amazing/incredible for every tribe &amp; ethnic group on the earth. That incredible news, is: [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Marge likes this rendering here for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Marge likes this rendering here for "gentiles" KT (Gal. "non-Jew" works well for that context)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kristus ada idop di bosong pung hati!<bt>Kristus is living in your livers!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Itu tu, yang bekin bosong parcaya tarús bilang,<bt>It is that which makes you continue to believe that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nanti Dia bekin hal-hal yang paling bae kasi sang bosong di sorga.<bt>He will do the best things for you in heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Marge likes this rendering of &quot;glory&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Marge likes this rendering of "glory" in this context; don't change it or regularise it ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ini ni, yang kotong manusia ada tunggu-tunggu dari dolu-dolu.<bt>It is this which we humans have been waiting/hoping for from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: the secret that has been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: the secret that has been kept hidden for ages and from generations, but is now shown to the saints. LITERALLY: To them among the Gentiles God has chosen to make known the glorious riches of this secret, which is Christ in you, the hope of glory.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Jadi botong kasi tau samua orang so'al Kristus. Botong ajar samua orang, deng kasi inga samua orang, pake samua akal yang Tuhan Allah kasi sang botong. Botong bekin bagitu, ko bekin tamba kuat samua orang yang iko sang Kristus, sampe dong jadi langkáp ko nanti dong bisa badiri di Dia pung muka deng sonde malu, tagal dong hati lurus tarús.<bt>So (consequently) we tell/explain to everyone about Kristus. We teach everyone, and warn/remind everyone, using every idea/reason/tactic that God gives to us. We do this, so make everyone who believes in Kristus even stronger, to the point they become complete so that later they can stand before Him without shame, because they continue to have straight/correct/right livers. [EXEG: revised 2015 to better reflect meaning of Gk /teleios/ ‘mature, perfect, complete’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nouthetountes: &quot;tell dem how dey gotta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">nouthetountes: "tell dem how dey gotta make", contextual adaptation from all other usages.* LITERALLY: We preach him, counseling/warning every person and teaching every person with all wisdom, so that we may present every person perfect/mature in Christ.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Andia ko beta pasang kaki deng karjá banting tulang kasi sang bosong. Beta bisa batahan karjá karás bagitu, tagal Kristus pung kuasa yang kasi kuat sang beta. Deng Dia pung kuasa tu, talalu hebat!<bt>That is why I fasten my feet (strive, exert, struggle for) and work extra hard (Idiom: work tossing bones) for you-pl. I can persevere working hard like that, because Kristus' power/authority is what gives me strength. And that power/authority of His, is absolutely amazing/incredible!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For this I labor, struggling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For this I labor, struggling with the energy he powerfully works/activates in me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Bosong yang tenga di kota Kolose, ais dong yang tenga di kota Laodikia, deng dong yang balóm parná katumu sang beta. Dengar bae-bae! Beta mau ko samua tau beta pung karjá karás kasi sang bosong, deng kasi sang dong.<bt>You who live in the city of Kolose, and2 those who live in the city of Laodikia, and those who have never yet met me! Listen up! I want for everyone to know of my hard work for you-pl, and for them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="helikos: how great agwn: struggle, fight,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">helikos: how great agwn: struggle, fight, conflict, inward conflict, anxiety, earnest concern, care, prayer<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: For I want you to how great is my anxiety/struggle for you, and for those in Laodicea, and for as many as have not seen me face to face,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Beta pung maksud, mau kasi kuat dong samua pung hati, ko dong ju bisa ta'ika jadi satu tagal dong idop basayang. Ais dong jadi yakin, tagal dong su mangarti batúl Tuhan pung maksud yang dolu ada tasambunyi. Itu rahasia tu, andia Kristus!<bt>My purpose is to strengthen/encourage all of their livers, so they can also be bound/joined becoming one/united because they are living in mutual love. So they are assured/confident, because they truly understand God2's purpose which was previously hidden. That secret, is Kristus!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Ais dong bisa tau batúl, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">(Ais dong bisa tau batúl, bilang, dong mangarti itu hal-hal bae samua tu. Te nanti dong mangarti Tuhan pung maksud samua kasi kotong.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: comfort, strengthen, encourage sumbibazw: unite,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">parakalew: comfort, strengthen, encourage sumbibazw: unite, knit together, bind together<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>ploutos: riches, wealth plerophoria: certainty, assurance<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>sunesis: insight, understanding epignwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>musterion: secret, mystery, something hidden LITERALLY: that their hearts may be encouraged, as they are knit together in love, to have the [riches of assured understanding / full assurance of understanding], for the knowledge of God's mystery, of Christ,<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Kalo bosong ta'ika jadi satu hati deng Kristus, baru Dia kasi samua akal yang bosong parlú, deng ajar bosong pake itu akal ko bekin hal-hal yang bae. Ini akal dong ni, sama ke harta pusaka yang mahal.<bt>If you are bound/joined becoming one liver (in accord, in harmony, same purpose) with Kristus, only then will He give you every idea/reason/tactic that you need, and teach you to use that idea to do things that are good. This idea, is like an expensive heirloom. [NOTE to daughter translations: In Gk. treasures hidden is plural, if your grammar needs to distinguish.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Samua pintar ada tasimpan dalam Kristus,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Samua pintar ada tasimpan dalam Kristus, sama ke orang simpan harta pusaka yang mahal dong. Deng cuma Dia sandiri sa yang bisa kasi tabuka, ko orang bisa mangarti batúl Tuhan Allah pung maksud tu.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thesauros: treasure sophia: wisdom [general, larger,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">thesauros: treasure sophia: wisdom [general, larger, higher], power of reasoning about truths and applying them to life<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>gnwsis: knowledge [specific], understanding of truths apokruphos: hidden, concealed<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: in whom are all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge hidden.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Beta kasi tau sang bosong ini hal dong samua, ko biar jang ada orang yang datang putar-balek sang bosong deng mulu manis.<bt>I tell/explain to you all these things, so that there is nobody who can come and deceive/trick you with a sweet mouth (=smooth talking).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paralogizomai: be deceived, be deluded, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">paralogizomai: be deceived, be deluded, be fooled, be led atray pithanologia: persuasive speech, beguiling words, enticing words, false arguments, fine sounding arguments, attractive arguments<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: I say this in order that none of you may be fooled with persuasive words.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Beta memang jao dari bosong. Biar bagitu, ma beta sonde lupa sang bosong, tagal beta pung hati ada ta'ika deng bosong. Deng beta sanáng, tagal beta tau bosong ada idop pantas, deng bosong masi pegang kuat bosong pung parcaya sang Kristus.<bt>It is true that I am far from you. Even that being the case, nevertheless I do not forget you, because my liver is bound to you. And I am happy, because I know that you are living appropriately, and you continue to hold strongly to your faith in Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeimi: absent xaipw: rejoice, be glad,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">apeimi: absent xaipw: rejoice, be glad, have joy<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>taksis: fixed order, order, orderly arrangement [military metaphor] sterewma: firmness, solid, steadfastness, stability<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pneumati: with you in Spirit, cf. 1 Cor 5:3 "No matta I no stay dea wit you guys, my heart stay dea." ;"even if" = relationship close; "no matta" = relationship not affected, = neva mind DM.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: For though absent in body, I am with you in spirit, rejoicing to see your good order and the firmness of your faith in Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong yang ta'ika deng Kristus dapa idop yang batúl<bt>We who are bound/joined with Kristus, get real life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tagal dolu bosong su tarima sang Yesus Kristus jadi bosong pung Bos, andia ko sakarang, bosong musti dengar tarús sang Dia. Te Dia tu, masi jadi bosong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang bosong.<bt>Because formerly you have received/accepted Yesus Kristus as your Boss, that is why now, you must continue to listen to/obey Him. Cuz (elaboration) He is still your Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As therefore you received Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As therefore you received Christ Jesus the Lord, live in him,</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-06-12 04:03:12Z" /></Annotation><v n="7" />Kalo bosong idop ta'ika deng Dia bagitu, bosong sama ke pohon yang batamba kuat, tagal dia pung akar tatanam dalam-dalam. Deng bosong sama ke ruma yang kuat, tagal bangun di atas fanderen yang kuat. Bosong bakuat tarús dalam bosong pung parcaya, sama ke yang bosong su parná balajar. Biar ko bosong pung hati maspurak deng rasa sukur, tagal samua hal yang Tuhan Allah su bekin kasi sang bosong.<bt>If you-pl live bound/joined to Him like that, you are like a tree which keeps growing stronger, because its roots are buried/planted deep. And you are like a strong house, because it is built on top of a strong foundation. You keep gaining strength in your faith, just like you once learned. May your livers erupt/artesian with gratitude, because of everything that God has done for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong musti baakar di dalam Dia,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Bosong musti baakar di dalam Dia, deng isap ame samua yang bae buat bosong pung idop dari Dia. Deng bagitu, bosong pung parcaya musti tamba kuat, sama ke yang bosong su dapa ajar dari kotong. Biar bosong pung idop ponu deng minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah tagal samua yang Dia su bekin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rizow: cause to take root, fix"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">rizow: cause to take root, fix firmly epoikodomew: build onto something<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>bebaiow: establish, strengthen, confirm perisseuw: be abundant, overflow, be outstanding, excel<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: rooted and built up in him, and established in the faith, just as you were taught, abounding in thanksgiving.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ati-ati ko bosong jang iko orang laen yang pake manusia pung akal, ko bawa serong sang bosong kaluar dari jalan lurus. Deng jang iko manusia pung ajaran pintar yang sonde ada pung dasar. Te dong pung ajaran tu, cuma datang dari manusia pung akal, deng dari dunya pung atoran dong. Ma itu ajaran dong, sonde ba'akar dalam Kristus.<bt>Be careful that you do not follow/obey other people who use human ideas/tactics, to lead you off-path away from the straight path. And don't follow humans' clever teaching that is unfounded. Cuz their teaching, just comes from human ideas, and from the regulations/principles of the world. But those teachings are not planted/buried in Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="blepw: watch, look, see sulagwgew: carry"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">blepw: watch, look, see sulagwgew: carry off as booty or captive, plunder<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>philosophia: philosophy [false teaching] kenos: empty, vain, futile, useless<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>apate: deceit, deception paradosis: tradition<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>stoixeion: fundamental principles, basic principles LITERALLY: See to it that no one takes you captive by human philosophy and empty deceit, according to human tradition, according to the basic principles of the universe, and not according to Christ.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Samua yang ada dalam Tuhan Allah pung diri, ju ada dalam Kristus pung diri. Deng Kristus ju jadi manusia, sama ke kotong.<bt>Everything that exists in God's Being/Self, also exists in Kristus' Being/Self. And Kristus is also human, just like us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katoikew: dwell, live, inhabit, settle down"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">katoikew: dwell, live, inhabit, settle down plerwma: fullness, that which fills, full measure<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>theotes: deity, Godhead swmatikws: bodily, corporeally, assume a bodily form, become incarnate<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: For in him the whole fulness of deity dwells bodily.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Tagal bosong ta'ika deng Kristus, deng jadi Dia pung orang, andia ko Dia bekin bosong jadi langkáp. Te Dia lebe tinggi dari samua kuasa deng samua yang pegang parenta, biar yang bae ko yang jahat.<bt>Because you are bound to Kristus, and have become His people, that is why He is/has made you to be complete. Cuz (elaboration) He is higher than all power/authority and all that hold rule/government, whether good or evil. [NOTE: Gk /kephalē/ not &gt; KM /kapala/ here to avoid saying that Kristus is Head of evil spirits] [NOTE to daughter translations: if “make you complete” is too vague, consider expanding to “langkáp dalam bosong pung sayang deng hal yang batúl dong” ‘complete in matters of love and truth’ (Ex. Summ.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plerow: make full, fill [with powers,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">plerow: make full, fill [with powers, qualities, etc.], complete kephale: head, leader<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>arche: ruler, authority exousia: power, bearer of authority, ruler<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: And you have been made full/complete in him, who is the head of all rule and authority.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu sunat, orang Yahudi dong potong buang &lt;burung&gt; pung ujung kulit ko jadi tanda bilang, dong tu, Tuhan Allah pung orang. Waktu bosong maso jadi Kristus pung orang, bosong ju kaná &lt;sunat&gt;. Dia pung maksud bagini: ini sunat bukan so'al orang potong buang kulit di badan, ma so'al Kristus potong buang hal-hal jahat dari kotong pung hati. Andia, hal-hal jahat yang kotong suka bekin tagal kotong ni, manusia.<bt>When circumcised, the Yahudi people cut off the tip of the skin of the 'bird' (polite euphemism for male genitals) as a sign that they are God's people. When you entered to become Kristus' people, you were also 'circumcised'. What it means is like this: this circumcision was not about cutting off skin on the body, but about Kristus cutting off/out the evil things/issues from our-inc livers. That is, evil things which we like to do because we are human.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="potong buang kulit pung ujung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">potong buang kulit pung ujung</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In whom also you were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In whom also you were circumcised by a circumcision made without hands, in the putting off of the body of flesh, in the circumcision of Christ,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Waktu dong sarani sang bosong pake aer, itu sama ke bosong iko takubur sama-sama deng Kristus. Ais bosong ju dapa idop baru, sama ke Dia ju dapa idop baru. Bosong dapa bagitu, tagal bosong parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah pake Dia pung kuasa yang hebat, ko kasi idop kambali sang Yesus Kristus dari Dia pung mati. Dia ju pake itu kuasa ko karjá di bosong pung hati.<bt>When they *baptised you-pl using water, that was like you participated in being buried together with Kristus. So/and/then you also got new life, just like He also got new life. You got it like that, because you believed that God used His incredible power/authority, to bring Yesus Kristus back to life from His death. He also used that power to work in your livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and buried with him in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and buried with him in baptism, in which you are raised with him through faith in the working of God, who raised him from the dead.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 6:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dolu bosong sama ke su mati, tagal bosong ada pung sala macam-macam, deng bosong balóm maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang. Biar bagitu, ma Dia hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong samua, deng kasi idop baru sang bosong, sama ke Dia kasi idop kambali sang Kristus.<bt>Formerly you were as if you had already died, because you had various *wrongs, and you had not yet become God's people. Even that being the case, nevertheless He wiped away all your wrongs, and gave new life to you, just like He brought Kristus back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraptwmais: trespass, false step, transgression, sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">paraptwmais: trespass, false step, transgression, sin akrobustia: uncircumcision [alienation from God]<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>suzwopoiew: make alive together [same time? / jalike?] xarizomai: forgive, pardon, remit "hemo da shame fo ...?" "take away da shame fo ...?" "let you guys go fo ...?"<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: And you, being dead in trespasses and the uncircumcision of your flesh, he made you alive together with him, having forgiven us all our trespasses,</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 2:1-8</note><v n="14" />Yang batúl tu, kotong musti kaná hukum, tagal kotong su langgar Tuhan Allah pung atoran dong. Ma Dia su hapus buang kotong pung hukuman dong, waktu dong paku sang Kristus di kayu palang.<bt>The correct thing, would be that we-inc should be punished, because we have transgressed God's regulations. But He has wiped away our punishments, when they nailed Kristus on the *cross. [DISCOURSE: depersonified, original put in footnote.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eksaleiphw: remove, destroy, obliterate, rubbing off"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">eksaleiphw: remove, destroy, obliterate, rubbing off xeirographon: document, indictment, hand-written certificate, certificate of indebtedness, bond<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>dogma: decree, proclamation, decision, ordinance, legal demand, legal requirement hupenantios: opposed, against, contrary<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>airw: set aside, take away, remove mesos: the middle<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>proselow: to nail firmly LITERALLY: having removed the legal indictment that stood against us, which was opposed to us, he set it aside, nailing it to the cross;<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma Dia su hapus buang kotong pung hukuman dong, tagal Dia su paku ame itu hukuman di Kristus pung kayu palang.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, "But He has wiped away our punishments, because He has nailed those punishments to Kristus' cross."</bt></note><note reference="2:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 2:15</note><v n="15" />Di situ, Dia kasi kala kuasa-kuasa galáp deng samua yang ada parenta deng jahat. Ais Dia bekin malu sang dong di orang banya pung muka. Itu sama ke tantara manáng paráng, yang pulang bekin pawe kuliling, kasi tunju dong pung musu yang su kala dong.<bt>There (locative), He has beaten (caused to lose) the various powers of darkness, and every(one/thing) that is governing/ruling evilly. So He has shamed them before many people (=in public). That is like a soldier/army which is victorious in battle/war, who comes home and has a parade, to show/display their enemies who have been defeated.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taráng kampong = as in wedding"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">taráng kampong = as in wedding procession around village</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apekduomai: disarm, spoiled, strip of ruling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">apekduomai: disarm, spoiled, strip of ruling power, strip of arms arxe: ruler<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>eksousia: power deigmatizw: make an example of, mock, expose<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>parresia: openly, boldly, with confidence thriambeuw: lead someone in a triumphal procession<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: He disarmed the rulers and powers, and made a public example, triumphing over them in him/it [Christ/the cross/the victory procession].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kalo orang mau kasi jato sang bosong so'al atoran makan-minum, na, jang toe sang dong. Deng kalo orang mau bekin parkara deng bosong so'al hari-hari bae, ko, pesta bulan baru, ko, atoran hari barenti karjá, na, jang dengar sang dong.<bt>If people want to bring us down concerning regulations of eating-drinking, na, don't be concerned with/care about/pay attention to them. And if people want to make disputes/issues with you concerning holidays, or new moon feasts, or regulations about the days of rest, na, don't listen to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krinw: judge brwsis: eating, food|i(16) (16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">krinw: judge brwsis: eating, food<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>posis: drinking, drink meros: in part<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>heorte: festival, feast neomenia: new moon festival<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>sabbaton: rest day LITERALLY: Therefore let no one judge you in matters of food and drink, a festival or a new moon, or a sabbath,<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 14:1-6</note><v n="17" />Parkara macam itu dong, sonde pantíng! Te itu parkara dong cuma sama ke bayang-bayang sa, yang nanti ilang buang. Ma Kristus tu, yang asli. Dia tu, yang tenga tarús.<bt>Disputes/matters of those sorts are not important! Cuz those disputes are only like shadows, which will (completely) disappear. But Kristus is the original/substance. He is the one who remains forever. [NOTE: From consultant check and UNS responses, changed to explicate grounds of comparison.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Parkara macam itu dong, sonde pantíng!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Parkara macam itu dong, sonde pantíng! Te itu cuma bayang-bayang sa, dari hal-hal yang nanti muncul datang. Ma yang asli tu, andia Kristus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skia: shadow swma: body, [subtance, reality]|i(17)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">skia: shadow swma: body, [subtance, reality]<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: These are a shadow of what is to come, but the substance is of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Kalo orang mau kasi jato sang bosong, tagal bosong sonde iko atoran yang dong bekin sandiri, na, jang dengar. Te kalo bosong dengar sang dong, na, bosong sonde bisa tarima hal-hal yang bae yang Tuhan Allah mau kasi bosong. Ma ati-ati, é! Te memang ada orang yang suka cari jalan ko kasi jato sang bosong. Dong mau ko bosong musti bekin randá bosong pung diri, deng songgo sang Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga dong, tagal dong kira ada mimpi yang kasi tunju sang dong bagitu. Dong anggap diri lebe bae dari orang laen dong. Padahal sonde bagitu! Te dong pung pikiran sama ke manusia biasa sa.<bt>[NOTE: Following Hawaii] If people want to bring you down, because you do not follow/obey regulations which they have made/created themselves, na, don't listen. Cuz, if you listen to them, na, you will not be able to receive the various good things that God wants to give you. But be careful, é! Cuz there really are people who like to find ways to bring you down. They want for you to have to lower/humble/humiliate yourselves, and traditional-worship the *angels, because they think/assume there are dreams which have shown them (to do) that. They consider themselves better than other people. When in fact, that is not the case! Cuz their thinking is merely like that of normal humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anggelos: angel eike: without cause, fo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">anggelos: angel eike: without cause, fo no reason<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>embateuw: enter into, investigate closely thelon: willing, voluntarily<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>threskeia: religion, worship, religious service, cult, external rites katabrabeuw: condemn, disqualify<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>kenembateuw: make a misstep nous: the mind<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>horaw: see, have a vision tapeinophrosune: humility, modesty, false humility<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>phusiow: blow up, puff up, inflate LITERALLY: Let no one disqualify you, by voluntary [/false] humility and worship of angels, entering into things which he has seen, puffed up for no reason by a sensuous mind,<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Dong sonde ta'ika deng Kristus. Padahal Dia tu, Kapala. Deng Dia pung orang-orang dong, sama ke Dia pung badan yang Dia ator. Dia bekin Dia pung orang dong batamba kuat, pake Tuhan Allah pung kuasa. Deng bagitu, dong jadi sama ke urat deng tulang yang bata'ika kuat ko batolong satu deng satu, sampe badan anteru bisa karjá deng bae.<bt>They are not bound with Kristus. When in fact, He is Head. And His people are like His body which He organises/regulates/controls. He makes His people to be increasingly strong/influential, using God's power. In that way, they are like tendons and bones which are strongly connected to each other to mutually help one another, to the point that the entire body can work well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bata'ika"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">bata'ika</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="auxanw: to grow auxeesis: cause growth|i(19)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">auxanw: to grow auxeesis: cause growth<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>haphe: joint, connection sundesmos: bond, sinew, ligament<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>epixoregew: to support sumbibazw: unite, bring together<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>kratew: hold fast to something or someone kephalee: head<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: and not holding fast to the head, from whom the body, supported and brought together through its joints and ligaments, grows with a growth that is from God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Connect back to not connected with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Connect back to not connected with Christ? Reinforce Christ as Head?</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 4:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong ta'ika deng Kristus, kotong dapa idop baru<bt>If we are bound with Kristus, we get new life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Bosong su mati sama-sama deng Kristus. Ais bosong sonde ta'ika lai deng kuasa-kuasa galáp di ini dunya. Jadi akurang ko bosong masi iko tarús dunya pung atoran macam-macam? Dong bilang bagini:<bt>You have died together with Kristus. So you are no longer bound to the various powers of darkness in this world. So (consequently), why (the hell) are you still continuing to follow the various regulations/principles of the world? [NOTE: Over-all construction implies anger or frustration, strong chiding] They say like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apothneskw: die dogmatizw: submit to rules|i(20)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">apothneskw: die dogmatizw: submit to rules<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>stoixeion: fundamental principles, basic spirits [see 2:8] LITERALLY: If you died with Christ to the basic principles of the world, why do you live as if you still belonged to the world and submit to them,<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />&lt;&lt;Jang pegang ini; jang makan itu; jang sonto ini.&gt;&gt;<bt>"Don't hold this; don't eat that; don't touch/feel this."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haptw: touch, handle, take hold of,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">haptw: touch, handle, take hold of, hold geuomai: taste, eat<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>thiganw: touch LITERALLY: "Do not handle, do not taste, do not touch,"<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ma itu atoran dong tu, cuma manusia yang bekin, ko dong ajar kasi orang dong. Padahal itu atoran dong cuma ator hal-hal yang nanti ilang buang sa!<bt>But those regulations are only made by humans, for them to teach people. When in fact those regulations only regulate/deal with matters which will later disappear!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entalma: commandment phthora: ruin, destruction, dissolution,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">entalma: commandment phthora: ruin, destruction, dissolution, deterioration, corruption<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>apoxresis: consume, use up LITERALLY: referring to things which are all destroyed as they are used, according to rules and teachings of human beings?<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Andekata orang bisa bekin iko itu atoran dong, dong kira nanti orang hormat sang dong, deng anggap dong talalu pintar, orang alim batúl, orang randá hati, orang yang siksa dong pung badan sandiri, deng tukang songgo yang rajin talalu. Padahal sonde! Itu atoran dong sonde bisa ator bekin bae manusia pung pikiran deng manusia pung hati yang kapingin bekin jahat!<bt>If it were the case [+hypothetical] that someone (actually) could do according to those regulations, they think that people will respect/honour them, and consider them really clever, people who are truly religious/spiritual, people who are humble, people who abuse/torment their own bodies, and people who are heavily involved in traditional-worship (excessively diligent at it). When in actual fact, that is not the case! Those regulations cannot arrange/regulate/control/deal with fixing/healing humans' thoughts and humans' livers that desire to do evil! [EXEG: The regulations? or the keeping of the regs? CEV “Obeying the regs”; to go abstract would make it bland and not vivid, perhaps distracting from Paul's intent here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balagu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">balagu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apheidia: severe treatment, severity, rigor ethelothreskia:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">apheidia: severe treatment, severity, rigor ethelothreskia: self-made religion, self-imposed worship, voluntary devotion<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>plesmone: satisfaction, gratification, indulgence tapeinophrosune: humility, modesty, self-abasement, [false humility]<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>time: honor, value LITERALLY: These indeed have the appearance of wisdom, in rigor of worship, self-abasement, severity to the body, but are of no value in checking the indulgence of the flesh.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo kotong lia itu atoran dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Kalo kotong lia itu atoran dong bagitu sa, tingka ke bagus, tagal dia ator ibadat yang bagus, renda hati, siksa diri. Padahal itu samua cuma mau bekin puas daging sa, ma sonde bekin bae orang pung pikiran deng hati yang kapingin hal-hal yang jahat.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Tuhan Allah su kasi bosong idop baru, sama ke Dia bekin bosong idop kambali sama-sama deng Kristus. Sakarang Kristus ada dudu di tampa paling hormat di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan. Andia ko bosong musti bapikir hal-hal yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati.<bt>God has given you new life, just like He has brought you back to life together with Kristus. Now Kristus is sitting in the most respected place at God's right side. That is why you must think (intentionally) about things/matters/issues that please God2's liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunegeirw: rise up with, be raised,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">sunegeirw: rise up with, be raised, resurrect. Like Romans 6:8 syzeesomen. zetew: seek, look for, desire to possess something<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>anw: above kathemai: sit<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>deksios: right side, right hand LITERALLY: Since therefore you have been raised with Christ, seek the things that are above, where Christ is seated at the right side of God;<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note><v n="2" />Pikir tarús-tarús so'al hal-hal yang Tuhan suka. Jang pusing deng hal-hal yang cuma bekin sanáng manusia pung hati sa.<bt>Keep thinking about things/matters/issues that God2 likes. Don't be concerned about things that merely please the livers of humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phronew: set one's mind on, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">phronew: set one's mind on, be intent on, think about, ponder, concentrate on LITERALLY: set your minds on the things that are above, not on the things that are on the earth;<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te bosong ju iko mati waktu Kristus mati. Ais bosong pung idop baru tu, aman, tagal su ta'ika deng Kristus yang ada sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah di sorga.<bt>Cuz you also participated in death when Kristus died. So that new life of yours, is secure/safe, because (you) are bound with Kristus, who is together with God in heaven. [EXEG: Gk /kekruptai/ as 'kept safe', not 'hidden', see LN 21.12]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apothneskw: die zwe: life|i(3) (3) |rkruptw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">apothneskw: die zwe: life<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>kruptw: hide, conceal, cover, safe, secure/ unseen, invisible, out of sight, (spiritual) LITERALLY: for you died, and your life has been hidden with Christ in God.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te bosong ju iko mati waktu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Te bosong ju iko mati waktu Kristus mati. Ais bosong pung idop yang batúl sonde kantara di ini dunya (lai), ma ta'ika deng Kristus, yang ada sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah di sorga.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Kristus ada idop dalam bosong pung hati, deng Dia ju bekin bosong idop batúl. Nanti waktu Dia datang kambali, bosong ju muncul sama-sama deng Dia. Itu samua tu, talalu hebat!<bt>[NOTE: structure following HCE] Kristus is living in your-pl livers, and He has also made you truly live. Later, when He comes back, you will also appear together with Him. All of that is too incredible/amazing! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(al) Ais, nanti waktu Tuhan Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">(al) Ais, nanti waktu Tuhan Allah kasi tunju sang samua orang di ini dunya, bilang, Kristus tu, sapa, na, Dia ju kasi tunju sang bosong. Deng bosong ju iko ame bagian deng Dia pung hebat tu.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phanerow: appear, show, reveal, come doksa:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">phanerow: appear, show, reveal, come doksa: glory, brightness, splendor, radiance<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: When Christ appears, who is our life, then you also will appear with him in glory.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-26 11:54:24Z">[EXEG: GK: glory here]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Idop model lama, deng idop model baru<bt>The old model/pattern of life, and the new model of life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Andia ko bosong musti angka buang bosong pung kapingin bekin jahat dong. Conto ke: kapingin maen serong deng orang yang bukan lu pung laki ko lu pung bini; kapingin bekin hal-hal kamomos dong; kapingin bekin iko lu pung hawa nafsu; kapingin bekin jahat macam-macam; deng saraka yang cuma mau samua jadi lu pung sa (padahal itu sama ke lu ada songgo, te lu angka tinggi-tinggi sang hal laen yang seti buang sang Tuhan).<bt>That is why you-pl must get rid of your desires/ tendencies to do evil. For example: the desire to play around (lit. play off-track, implies sexually) with someone who is not your-sg husband or your wife; the desire to do filthy/defiling things; the desire to follow along with your carnal passions/desires; the desire to do various sorts of evil; and selfishness/greediness which only wants everything to just be yours-sg (when in fact, that is the same as you being involved in traditional-worship, cuz you are elevating other things which elbow God2 out of the way).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nekrow: put to death melos: member,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">nekrow: put to death melos: member, part, limb<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>porneia: prostitution, fornication, any kind of sexual immorality akatharsia: impurity, uncleanness, dirt, immorality, viciousness<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pathos: passion, sexual passion epithumia: desire, longing, desire for something forbidden<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>kakos: bad, evil pleoneksia: greediness, covetousnesss, a desire to have more<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>eidwlolatria: idolatry, worship of idols LITERALLY: Therefore, put to death what is earthly in you: immorality, impurity, passion, evil desire, and the desire to have more, which is idolatry,<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Itu hal dong yang bekin Tuhan Allah mara talalu, sampe Dia mau kasi hukum sang samua orang yang sonde mau dengar sang Dia.<bt>Those issues are ones that make God extremely angry, to the point that He wants to punish all people who do not want to listen to/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Tuhan sonde mau tahan Dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">(Tuhan sonde mau tahan Dia pung mara sang dong lai)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orge: wrath, anger, indignation, (judgment) apeitheia:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">orge: wrath, anger, indignation, (judgment) apeitheia: disobedience<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: because of which the wrath of God is coming on the sons of disobedience;</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Dolu bosong ju idop bagitu, te bosong pung hati ta'ika deng itu hal jahat dong.<bt>Previously you also lived like that, cuz your livers were bound by those sorts of evil issues.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peripatew: walk around, live, conduct oneself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">peripatew: walk around, live, conduct oneself zaw: live, conduct of life<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: in which you also once walked when you lived in them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma sakarang bosong musti angka buang bosong pung rasa kapingin bekin jahat samua. Conto ke: suka mara; hati panas; simpan hati; omong bekin rusak orang pung nama bae; deng mulu kotor.<bt>But now you must get rid of all of your desires to do evil. For example: easily angered, excessive anger (Idiom: hot liver), resentment (Idiom: stored liver), speaking to damage people's good name; and dirty mouth (=filthy speech).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apotithemi: put away, lay aside orge:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">apotithemi: put away, lay aside orge: wrath, anger, indignation,<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>thumos: anger, wrath, rage kakia: malice, badness, morally faulty, ill-will, wickedness, malicious gossip, desire to injure someone<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>blasphemia: slander, defamation of character, blasphemy aisxrologia: evil speech, obscene talk, abusive speech<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: But now, you also put away all anger, wrath, malice, slander, foul talk from your mouth;</Message></Annotation><v n="9-10" />Deng bosong satu deng satu jang baputar-balek. Tagal bosong su angka buang bosong pung hati yang kapingin bekin jahat, deng kasi tenga bosong pung jalan idop yang lama.<bt>And each of you should not be deceiving/lying/conning/cheating each other. Because you have gotten rid of your livers that desire to do evil, and have left behind/abandoned your old way of life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pseudomai: lie apekduomai: take off, put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">pseudomai: lie apekduomai: take off, put off<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>palaios: old praksis: practice, deed, action, activity<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: do not lie to each other, because you have taken off the old nature with its practices,</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 4:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Deng sakarang bosong su ganti sang dia, pake hati yang baru. Itu sama ke orang angka buang dia pung pakean lama yang dadolek dong, ko pake pakean baru yang barisi. Tuhan Allah yang bekin ame sang bosong. Deng sakarang Dia ju bekin bosong tamba mangarti sang Dia, deng bekin bosong ko lama-lama jadi satu model ke Dia.<bt>And now you have replaced it, using/wearing a new liver. That is like a person taking off/getting rid of his old filthy clothes/shirt, to use/wear clean new clothes. God is the one who created you. And now He also makes you increasingly understand Him, and makes you to eventually become the same model/type as Him. [EXEG: At best Gk is ambiguous between a) the original creator in the normal use of the word; 2) the catalyst of constant renewal of the new being/regeneration; most translations are able to preserve the ambiguity; and #1 does not preclude or exclude the role of renewal in this context; whereas making #2 explicit (as TEV) does, excludes #1, and I think goes beyond the text in this instance; Our protocols here include a) preserve ambiguity where possible where both readings are supported, and follow TB if it is supported and Team chose that (which they often don't, but here they did). So the solution from the OV is to remove/delete (long ago).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="puruk = worn out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">puruk = worn out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enduw: put on, get dressed neos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">enduw: put on, get dressed neos: new<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>anakainow: renew, make new epignwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>eikwn: form, image, likeness LITERALLY: and have put on the new nature, which is being renewed in knowledge according to the image of its creator,<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:26, Efesus 4:24</note><v n="11" />Dalam idop baru ni, kotong sonde bacáp orang dari dong pung kulit luar bilang, dong tu orang Yahudi ko, orang bukan Yahudi ko; orang yang iko sunat ko, orang yang sonde sunat ko; orang asing ko, orang biadab ko;<bt>In this new life, we-inc do not brand people from their outside skin saying, they are Yahudi people, or not Yahudi people (or whatever); they are people who have participated in circumcision, or people who have not been circumcised (or whatever); foreigners, or ill-mannered/uncivilised (or whatever); slaves, or free people (or whatever). It is not those things that are important! But what is important, is if/whether they are bound with Kristus, and whether He is living in their livers.</bt><note reference="3:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;orang Barbar deng orang Skutia&gt;&gt;. Dong cap orang Barbar tu, orang asing yang ada di luar kuasa pamarenta Roma. Deng dong cap orang Skutia tu, orang biadab.<bt>The Yunani language Bible, writes saying, "Barbar people and Skutia people". They branded Barbar people as foreigners outside the authority of the Roma government. And they branded Skutia people, as ill-mannered/uncivilised people.</bt></note>budak ko, orang bebas ko. Bukan itu yang pantíng! Ma yang pantíng, kalo dong ta'ika deng Kristus, deng kalo Dia ada idop di dong pung hati.<bt>slaves, or free people (or whatever). It is not those things that are important! But what is important, is if/whether they are bound with Kristus, and whether He is living in their livers. [NOTE to daughter translations: “free man” can refer to 1) those who used to be slaves, and/or 2) those who never were slaves; careful to not use vocab that implies “freed from prison”, or “liberated (politically)”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Here there cannot be Greek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Here there cannot be Greek and Jew, circumcised and uncircumcised, barbarian, Scythian, slave, free man, but Christ is all, and in all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang bosong, tagal Dia sayang sang bosong. Dia pung maksud ko bosong jadi Dia pung orang barisi yang beda dari manusia biasa. Andia ko bosong musti jadi orang yang pung hati manis, hati bae, randá hati, hati lumbu, deng hati sabar.<bt>God has chosen you, because He loves/pities you. His purpose/intention is for you to be/become His clean/pure/holy people who are different from normal humans. That is why you must be/become people who have sweet livers (gentle, kind), good livers (kind, generous, gracious), low livers (humble), soft livers (polite), and patient livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati noe = hati lembe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">hati noe = hati lembe = soft heart (implies weaknees of character), gampang dibujuk ; @@ hati lumbu = lembut, polite, sopan, sabar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="splagxon: inward parts oiktirmos: pity, mercy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">splagxon: inward parts oiktirmos: pity, mercy, compassion<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>xrestotes: goodness, kindness, generosity, desire for another's good tapeinophrosune: humility, humbleness, lowliness, modesty<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>prautes: gentleness, meekness, humility, courtesy, consideration makrothumia: longsuffering, patience, forbearance<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: Put on then, as God's chosen ones, holy and beloved, compassion, kindness, lowliness, meekness, patience,</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Bosong musti sabar deng mangarti satu deng satu. Kalo dari bosong ada yang bacari hal deng dia pung tamán, na, jang simpan hati. Ma bosong musti lupa buang itu sala, deng kasi ampon sang dia, sama ke Tuhan su lupa buang bosong pung sala.<bt>You must be patient and understanding with each other. If there are those among you who are (trying to) create issues with his companions/fellows, na, don't store your liver (build resentment). But you must (completely) forget about that wrong (addressing the heart), and grant forgiveness to him (addressing the social action), just like God2 has (completely) forgotten about your-pl wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anexw: put up with, endure, bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">anexw: put up with, endure, bear with, forbear xarizw: forgive, give freely. "hemo da shame from you?" "hemo da bad kine stuff from you?" "take away da shame?" "throw out da shame?" "let you guys go?" In this context of interpersonal relationships, "let um go" fits best, and it is all right if the same thing is attributed to God without adding all the details.<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>momphe: complaint, grievance, blame LITERALLY: bearing with others and forgiving each other, if anyone has a complaint against another; just as the Lord has also forgiven you, you also do the same;<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong musti sabar deng mangarti satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Bosong musti sabar deng mangarti satu deng satu. Kalo dari bosong ada orang yang bacari hal deng dia pung tamán ko mau kasi sala sang dia, na, bosong musti lupa buang itu sala, deng kasi ampon sang dia, sama ke Tuhan su lupa buang bosong pung sala-sala dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 4:2,32</note><v n="14" />Inga te sayang tu, lebe pantíng dari samua. Ais bosong musti pake sayang di bosong pung hati, sama ke orang pake pakean di badan. Te sayang tu, sama ke banáng yang kotong pake tanún ko bekin jadi kaen yang paling bagus. Itu yang ika sang kotong jadi satu.<bt>Remember that love is more important than everything. So you must wear love in/on your livers, just like people wear clothes on their bodies. Cuz that love (that I'm talking about), is like a thread which we-inc use to weave into a fine/beautiful piece of clothe. That is what binds/ties us together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tanún @@@ CALENDAR VERSE"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">tanún @@@ CALENDAR VERSE</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agape: love, intelligent and purposeful self-giving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">agape: love, intelligent and purposeful self-giving sundesmos: bond, bond that unites<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>teleiotes: perfection, maturity, completeness LITERALLY: and above all these, love, which binds everything together in perfection.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Kotong bisa badame deng Tuhan Allah, tagal Kristus. Jadi bosong ju musti kasi biar Kristus pung dame ator bosong pung hati. Te Tuhan mau ko bosong samua idop badame satu deng satu, tagal bosong samua ta'ika jadi satu badan. Deng bosong pung hati musti rasa sukur tarús, tagal Dia sandiri yang su pili ame sang bosong.<bt>We can have peace/reconciliation with God, because of Kristus. So (consequently) you must also allow that peace of Kristus to arrange/regulate/control your livers. Cuz God2 wants for you to live in relational-peace with each other, because you are all bound/tied/joined together as one body. And your livers must also be continually grateful, because He himself is the one who has chosen you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eirene: peace, inner peace (attitude of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">eirene: peace, inner peace (attitude of mind), tranquility, condition of rest, contentment brabeuw: rule, decide, control, judge, govern<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>kalew: call, summon, invite swma: body<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>euxaristos: thankful, grateful LITERALLY: Let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, to which you were called in one body, and be thankful.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kristus pung Kata-kata dong ju musti ator bosong pung hati deng bosong pung idop. Itu Kata-kata dong sama ke harta yang mahal, yang Dia kasi sang bosong. Dong kasi tunju jalan ko bosong bisa mangarti banya hal iko Tuhan pung pikiran. Ais bosong bisa pake sang dong ko ajar deng kasi inga bosong satu deng satu. Kalo ajar sang bosong pung orang dong, jang ajar deng kasar, ma pake hati manis yang ponu deng rasa sukur. Pake lagu puji dong, lagu rohani dong, deng lagu-lagu yang bosong sandiri karang ko angka puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Kristus' Words/Sayings/Message must also arrange/regulate/control your livers and your lives. Those Words are like expensive/valuable possessions which He has given you. They show the way for you to be able to understand many things, in accord with God2's thinking. So then you can use them to teach and remind/warn each other. If/when you teach them to people, don't teach with roughness/rudeness/abusive, but use a sweet liver (gentle, kind) which is full of gratitude [NOTE: deliberately trying to leave open toward God &amp; other people]. Use praise songs, and spiritual songs, and various songs that you yourselves have composed to lift praises to God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">karang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enoikew: live, dwell, be at home,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">enoikew: live, dwell, be at home, stay plousiws: richly, abundantly, in all its wealth of meaning and power, with its wide application to every sphere of life and experience<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>nouthetew: admonish, warn against error, instruct, stimulate, encourage, urge to forsake evil psalmos: psalm, song of praise, poems which are sung<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>humvos: hymn, song, praise to God wde: song, sacred song, any song<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>pneumatikos: spiritual, sung in the Spirit, voicing holy aspirations xaris: favor, grace, gift, thankfulness, gratitude<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>adw: sing LITERALLY: Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly in all wisdom, as you teach and admonish one another with psalms, hymns, spiritual songs, singing with thankfulness in your hearts to God;<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Bosong ni, su jadi Yesus Kristus pung wakil. Jadi inga te samua yang bosong omong, ada bawa Dia pung nama. Deng samua yang bosong bekin, ada bawa Dia pung nama ju. Ais jang lupa bekin samua-samua &lt;&lt;atas nama&gt;&gt; bosong pung Bos Yesus Kristus. Deng minta tarima kasi tarús sang Dia pung Bapa, Tuhan Allah.<bt>You have already become Yesus Kristus' representatives. So remember that everything that you say, is bearing His name/reputation. And everything that you do, is bearing His name/reputation. [NOTE: Deliberately kept separate.] So then do not forget to do everything "in the name of" your Boss, Yesus Kristus. [NOTE: This "in the name of" is a legal and administrative category.] And give thanks continually to His Father, God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And all things, whatever you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And all things, whatever you do, in word or in action, do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 5:19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Kristen dong musti idop karmana, satu deng satu?<bt>How should Kristen people live with each other?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bini dong! Bosong musti topang deng dengar sang bosong pung laki, tagal itu pantas kasi orang yang iko sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>Wives! You-pl must listen/obey your husbands, because that is appropriate for people who follow/obey Yesus Kristus. [NOTE: See discussion on meaning of the Gk term in Eph. 5. Not only ‘be subject’, but also ‘undergird, support’, (lit: stand under); And this more positive approach works better for the bidirectional broad mandate given to all believers in Eph 5:21.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupotassw: submit, be subject, subject yourself,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">hupotassw: submit, be subject, subject yourself, subordinate yourself, obey, be obedient, give way to, adapt yourself to, place yourself under anekw: be proper, fitting, appropriate<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: Wives, be subject to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong bini dong, musti tondo di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Bosong bini dong, musti tondo di bawa bosong pung laki, sama ke yang Tuhan Allah su ator ame.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 5:22, 1 Petrus 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Laki dong! Bosong musti sayang bosong pung bini, deng jang takán-takán sang dia, ko bekin dia pung hati saki.<bt>Husbands! You must love/pity your wives, and not keep oppressing her, so that (you) make her angry/resentful.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takán = oppress,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">takán = oppress,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapaw: love, active and unceasing care"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">agapaw: love, active and unceasing care for her well-being pikrainw: become bitter, be harsh to. "Make any kine" includes this, but doesn't highlight the husband's bad attitude as much pikrainein does.<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: Husbands, keep on loving your wives and do not be harsh to them.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 5:25, 1 Petrus 3:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ana-ana dong! Bosong musti topang deng dengar bosong pung orang tua dalam samua hal, te itu yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati.<bt>Children! You must listen/obey your parents in every issue/matter, cuz that is what pleases God2's liver. [EXEG: NLT, CEV, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupakouw: obey, listen to, follow, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">hupakouw: obey, listen to, follow, be subject to euarestos: pleasing, acceptable<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: Children, obey your parents in everything, for this pleases the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 6:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Orang tua dong! Jang maen takán deng karás sang ana-ana dong, ko biar dong sonde tawar hati deng basimpan hati sang bosong.<bt>Parents! Don't keep harshly/strictly oppressing/pressing your children, so that they have no feeling/lose heart (Idiom: tasteless liver) and are angry/resentful toward you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tawar hati = no feeling ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">tawar hati = no feeling ; (hati jato, hati barát, hati ancor, hati kakodok, hati manoso, pata samangat)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="erethizw: provoke to anger, embitter, exasperate,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">erethizw: provoke to anger, embitter, exasperate, drive to resentment, irritate, arouse athumew: lose heart, discourage<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: Parents, do not provoke your children to anger, so that they may not become discouraged.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 6:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Orang karjá dong! Di ini dunya, bosong musti bekin iko bosong pung bos dalam samua hal. Jang cuma cari-cari muka sa waktu dong ada lia-lia sang bosong. Ma usaha ko bosong salalu bekin sanáng sang dong. Karjá samua hal deng batúl, tagal bosong tau bilang, Tuhan Allah ada lia-lia sang bosong.<bt>Workers! In this world, you must follow/obey your bosses/masters in all matters. Don't just keep currying favour while they are checking up on you. But make the effort so that you are always making them happy. Do all your work correctly, because you know that God is checking up on you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupakouw: obey, listen to ophthalmodoulia: eye"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">hupakouw: obey, listen to ophthalmodoulia: eye service, work for appearances, work for show, service performed to attract attention<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>anthrwpareskos: men pleaser, looking for people's approval haplotes: sincerity, simplicity, singleness, uprightness, frankness<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>phobow: to fear, have respect for, have reverence for LITERALLY: Slaves, obey in everything your earthly masters, not with eyeservice, as menpleasers, but in singleness of heart, fearing the Lord.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong hamba-hamba dong, musti dengar deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Bosong hamba-hamba dong, musti dengar deng bekin iko bosong pung tuan pung mau dalam samua hal, jang cuma waktu bosong ada di dong pung muka sa ko bekin sanáng dong pung hati sabantar sa, ma bosong pung hati ju musti barisi deng dong, tagal bosong taku sang Tuhan Allah.</Message></Annotation><v n="23-24" />Bosong ada bekin apa sa, na, karjá yang batúl deng samangat. Bosong musti karjá macam ke bosong ada karjá kasi sang bosong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, bukan kasi manusia. Te bosong layani sang Dia. Deng nanti Dia yang balas bosong pung upa deng kasi pusaka sang bosong.<bt>Whatever you are doing, na, do it correctly with enthusiasm. You must work as if you are working for your Boss, Yesus Kristus, not for humans. Cuz you are serving Him. And He will be the one who will repay/reciprocate your reward/payment/wages and give you your inheritance.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ek psuxes: heartily, with all your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">ek psuxes: heartily, with all your heart, put your whole heart into it, from the soul, eagerly, zestfully LITERALLY: Whatever you do, work heartily for the Lord and not for people,<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>apolambanw: receive antapodosis: repaying, reward<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>kleronomia: inheritance, (eternal life) LITERALLY: because you know that you will receive the inheritance from the Lord as the reward. You serve the Lord Christ.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong tau, bilang, bosong nanti tarima"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Bosong tau, bilang, bosong nanti tarima ame bosong pung gaji paling bésar dari Tuhan Allah. Kristus tu Tuan, deng bosong ni Dia pung hamba dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ma kalo bosong sonde karjá deng batúl, nanti Dia hukum sang bosong. Te Dia adil, deng sonde bapili muka.<bt>But if you do not work correctly/right, He will punish you. Cuz He is just/fair (legal term), and doesn't play favourites/biased (Idiom: doesn't choose faces).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikew: do wrong, violate the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">adikew: do wrong, violate the law komizw: carry off, get, receive pay, receive wages, bring<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>proswpolempsia: partiality, favoritism, respect of persons LITERALLY: For the wrongdoer will be paid back for his wrongdoing, and without favoritism.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:22-25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 6:5-8; Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 10:17, Efesus 6:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Bos-bos dong! Bosong musti ator bosong pung tukang suru-suru dong deng batúl, deng adil. Inga te bosong ju ada pung Bos di sorga yang ator sang bosong.<bt>Bosses/masters! You must oversee/manage/organise/regulate your workers/servants correctly and fairly. Remember that you also have a Boss in heaven who oversees you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parexw: give, grant something to someone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">parexw: give, grant something to someone isotes: fair, 'fair and square'<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Masters, give your servants that which is just and fair, knowing that you also have a Master in Heaven.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 6:9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Macam-macam nasiat<bt>Various advice</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Bosong musti rajin sambayang tarús. Deng musti sadar so'al hal-hal yang bosong omong deng Tuhan Allah, deng sambayang pake hati yang ponu rasa sukur.<bt>You-pl must be diligent to keep praying. And (you) must be aware/informed about the things/matters that you speak/discuss with God, and pray using a liver which is full of gratitude.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="otak tajam = (forced) ; sadar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">otak tajam = (forced) ; sadar =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proskarterew: adhere to, persist in, busy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">proskarterew: adhere to, persist in, busy yourself with, be busily engaged in, be devoted to, continue in gregorew: be awake, stay awake, be on the alert, watch, be wide awake about it, be watchful<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: Be devoted to prayer, and stay alert in it with thanksgiving,</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jang lupa sambayang kasi sang botong, deng minta ko Tuhan Allah buka jalan, ko botong bisa kasi tau orang hal-hal yang dolu tasambunyi so'al Kristus. Inga te beta maso bui ni, tagal beta kasi tau orang so'al Kristus.<bt>Don't forget to pray for us-exc, and ask that God opens the way for us to be able to tell/explain to people matters which were previously hidden about Kristus. Remember that I have been put here in prison, because I have been telling people about Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: at the same time, praying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: at the same time, praying also for us, that God may open to us a door for the word, to declare the mystery of Christ, on account of which I have been put in prison,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Sambayang ko beta bisa kasi tau itu Kabar Bae deng jalás-jalás, ko biar orang bisa mangarti batúl.<bt>Pray that I can tell/explain that Good News with real clarity, so that people can understand it well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ VERSE on good communication"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">@@ VERSE on good communication</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: that I may make it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: that I may make it clear, as I ought to speak.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Idop deng batúl di teng-tenga orang yang balóm parcaya sang Kristus. Pake bae-bae tiap kasampatan yang Tuhan kasi sang bosong.<bt>Live right in the midst of people who do not yet believe in Kristus. Use well each opportunity which God2 give to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Conduct yourselves wisely toward outsiders,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Conduct yourselves wisely toward outsiders, making the most of the time.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 5:16</note><v n="6" />Kalo bosong omong, na, omong manis-manis yang kaná deng orang pung hati. Jang omong bekin bosan sang dong. Pake kata-kata yang batúl, ko bosong bisa manyao bale deng bae-bae, kalo ada orang yang tanya sang bosong.<bt>If/when you speak, na, speak sweetly (=nice in attitude and interesting in content; as opposed to speak dry-dry = monotone, cold, and uninteresting) in such a way as to connect with people's livers. Don't speak in ways that bore them. Use words that are true/correct, so you can be able to respond back well, if there are people who question you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karíng-karíng = sonde manarik, monotone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">karíng-karíng = sonde manarik, monotone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let your speech be always"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let your speech be always with grace, seasoned with salt, that you may know how you ought to answer every person.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo bosong omong, omong deng suara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">Kalo bosong omong, omong deng suara sayang, jang omong deng suara karing-karing sa. Deng bagitu, nanti bosong tau, bilang, bosong musti kasi jawab karmana deng samua orang yang datang batanya sang bosong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus tutu dia pung surat<bt>Paulus closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Nanti Tikikus mau datang carita kasi bosong so'al beta pung dudu-badiri. Dia tu, sodara yang botong sayang, yang layani Tuhan pung orang deng satia. Dolu dia kasi jalan Tuhan pung karjá sama-sama deng beta ju.<bt>Later Tikikus is going to come tell you about my situation (Idiom: sitting-standing). He is a sibling whom we-exc love, and serves God2's people with loyalty. Previously he also carried out God2's work together with me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Tychicus will make known to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Tychicus will make known to you all the things about me. He is a beloved brother, a faithful helper and fellow servant in the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 20:4, 2 Timotius 4:12</note><v n="8" />Beta utus sang dia bagitu, ko dia bisa pi kasi kuat bosong pung hati, deng bisa carita sang bosong so'al botong di sini.<bt>I sent/comissioned him like that, so he could go strengthen/encourage your livers, and could narrate to you about us here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have sent him to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have sent him to you for this purpose: that you may know the things about us, and he may encourage your hearts,</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 6:21-22</note><v n="9" />Beta ju kirim pulang sang Onesimus, ko iko sama-sama deng dia. Onesimus tu, sodara satia yang kotong sayang. Dia tu, bosong pung orang sandiri. Dong dua nanti carita sang bosong samua hal yang su jadi di sini.<bt>I am also sending home Onesimus, to accompany him. That Onesimus, is a loyal sibling whom we-inc love. He is one of you people. The two of them will narrate to you everything that has happened here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: With Onesimus, a faithful and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: With Onesimus, a faithful and beloved brother, who is from you. They will make known to you all things which have happened here,</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Filemon 10-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Aristarkus ada titip salam kasi bosong. Dong ada tahan sang dia di bui, sama-sama deng beta. Barnabas pung sapupu, nama Markus, ju ada titip salam. Dolu beta su pasán memang sang bosong bilang, kalo Markus datang lia sang bosong, na, tarima bae-bae sang dia.<bt>Aristarkus sends greetings to you. They are detaining him in prison together with me. Barnabas' cousin, named Markus, also sends greetings. Previously I had instructed you beforehand that, if Markus came to see you, na, receive him well/favourably. [NOTE to daughter translations: Many lgs do not have a generic word for cousin, so you'll have to discuss this. Commentaries are not clear on what the relationship is, but some think Barnabas was the nephew of Mary, who was John Mark's mother. Since we don't know how the link works, we suggest you map the roles. I.e. Barnabas functioned in a “kakak” role, and Mark in an “adik” role.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, greets"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, greets you, and Marcus, Barnabas's sister's son, concerning whom you received orders: if he comes to you, receive him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 19:29, 27:2, Filemon 24, Utusan dong pung Carita 12:12, 25, 13:13, 15:37-39</note><v n="11" />Yesus, (yang botong ju pange bilang, &lt;&lt;Yustus&gt;&gt;) ju titip salam kasi bosong. Dari samua tamán yang sama-sama kasi jalan Tuhan Allah pung karjá, cuma dong tiga sa yang jadi orang Kristen dari bangsa Yahudi. Dong ni, yang kasi kuat beta pung hati.<bt>Yesus (whom we also call "Yustus") also sends greetings to you. Among all the companions who together carry out the work of God, only those three are ones who have become Kristen people from the Yahudi people. And these are the ones who strengthen/encourage my liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And Jesus, who is called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And Jesus, who is called Justus. They are from the circumcision [group]. These are my only fellow workers for God's kingdom, who have been a comfort to me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Bosong pung tamán Epafras ada di sini, deng dia ada titip salam kasi bosong ju. Dia jadi Yesus Kristus pung orang suru-suru. Dia salalu sambayang ukur kuat kasi sang bosong, deng minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi kuat sang bosong, bekin langkáp sang bosong, deng bekin bosong mangarti batúl-batúl Dia pung mau.<bt>Your friend Epafras is here, and he also sends greetings to you. He is a servant/worker of Yesus Kristus. He always prays with all his might (measure strong) for you, and asks that God will make you strong, make you complete, and make you truly understand His will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Epaphras, who is from you,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Epaphras, who is from you, a servant of Christ, greets you, always laboring fervently for you in prayers, that you may stand mature and fully assured in all the will of God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 1:7, Filemon 23</note><v n="13" />Beta kasi tau memang sang bosong bilang, Epafras tu, su karjá banting tulang kasi sang bosong, deng kasi orang Kristen dong di kota Laodikia deng kota Herapolis.<bt>I am telling you directly that, Epafras had worked very hard (throwing bones) for you/for your benefit, and for the Kristen people in the city of Laodikia and the city of Herapolis.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I testify of him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I testify of him, that he works hard for you, and those in Laodicea, and those in Hierapolis.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ada salam dari Demas, deng dari dokter Lukas, yang kotong sayang.<bt>There are greetings from Demas, and from doctor Lukas, whom we love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Luke, the beloved physician, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas, greet you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Timotius 4:10, 11, Filemon 24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Beta titip salam kasi sodara orang parcaya dong yang ada di kota Laodikia. Jang lupa titip beta pung salam kasi Mama Nimfa deng orang-orang parcaya yang biasa bakumpul di dia pung ruma.<bt>I send greetings to the believing siblings who are in the city of Laodikia. Don't forget to pass on my greetings to Mama Nimfa and the believers who normally/often gather together in her house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Greet the brothers who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Greet the brothers who are in Laodicea, and Nymphas, and the church which is in her house.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Nanti kalo bosong samua di Kolose su baca abis ini surat, na, kirim tarús kasi orang parcaya di kota Laodikia ko dong ju bisa baca. Deng bosong ju musti baca surat yang beta parná kirim kasi sang dong.<bt>Later when all of you in Kolose have finished reading this letter, na, send it on to the believers in the city of Laodikia so that they can also read it. And you must also read the letter that I once sent to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when this letter is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when this letter is read among you, cause that it be read also in the church of the Laodiceans, and that you also read the letter from Laodicea.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Kasi inga sang Arkipus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu jang lupa kasi jalan sampe abis, itu tugas yang lu su tarima dari Tuhan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remind/warn Arkipus saying, "You-sg must not forget to carry out to completion, that job/responsibility which you received from God2."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ FINISHER verse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z">@@ FINISHER verse</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And say to Archippus, &quot;Take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And say to Archippus, "Take heed to the ministry which you have received in the Lord, that you fulfill it."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Filemon 2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Jang lupa bilang, dong masi tahan sang beta dalam ini bui.<bt>Don't forget that they are still detaining me in this prison.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong.<bt>I ask that God show His goodness/kindness/grace/favour to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <span class="Italic">Lia sa, te ini surat, beta teken pake beta pung tangan sandiri,</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">Look at this, cuz (elaboration) this letter I have signed using my own hand,</span>
      </bt>
      <Annotation class="General" selectedText="meth' hymoon: a little different from">
        <Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:54:39Z" status="Information">meth' hymoon: a little different from hymiin. LITERALLY: The greeting by the hand of Paul. Remember my bonds. Grace be with you.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message>
      </Annotation>
    </p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <span class="Italic">Salam dari beta,</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">Greeting/leavetaking from me,</span>
      </bt>
    </p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <span class="Italic">Paulus</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">Paulus</span>
      </bt>
    </p>
  </book>
</bible>